Industry Context

This is a common Tier 1 Service Desk incident. Users working remotely frequently lose access to mapped network drives when the VPN is disconnected or when a drive fails to reconnect after sign-in. The standard troubleshooting process is to verify VPN connectivity, confirm the correct shared folder with the user, obtain the approved UNC path from the organization's knowledge base, and remap the network drive if necessary. Before closing the ticket, technicians should always verify that the drive is visible in This PC and that the user can open the shared folder successfully.
